    "question_text": "What is the value of 3 + 4 \u00d7 2 \u2212 1?",
    "question_format": "multiple_choice",
    "answer_choices": {
      "A": "13",
      "B": "10",
      "C": "14",
      "D": "7"
    },
    "correct_answer": "B",
    "explanation": "Apply multiplication before addition and subtraction. 4 \u00d7 2 = 8. Then evaluate left to right: 3 + 8 \u2212 1 = 11 \u2212 1 = 10.",
    "distractor_logic": {
      "A": "Student adds before multiplying: (3 + 4) \u00d7 2 \u2212 1 = 7 \u00d7 2 \u2212 1 = 14 \u2212 1 = 13.",
      "B": "Correct: 3 + (4 \u00d7 2) \u2212 1 = 3 + 8 \u2212 1 = 10.",
      "C": "Student adds first and then forgets to subtract: (3 + 4) \u00d7 2 = 14, ignoring the \u2212 1.",
      "D": "Student groups incorrectly, treating the expression as 3 + 4 \u00d7 (2 \u2212 1) = 3 + 4 = 7."
    },
    "difficulty_level": "Basic",
    "difficulty_b": null,
